SIMPLE: axerophthol
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: axerophthol
<hw>axerophthol</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a vitamin essential
for normal vision (<chform>C20H30O</chform>); it prevents night
blindness or inflammation or dryness of the eyes; same as
<altname>vitamin A</altname>. One U.S.P. unit of vitamin A is equivalent
to 0.30 micrograms of pure vitamin A alcohol.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> vitamin A; vitamin A alcohol; antiophthalmic factor;
biosterol; retinol; A.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Axial</ent>⟦br⟧
